description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Occupational Therapist ( fixed term contract until May 2021 - maternity cover) 37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Occupational Therapist to join the Elderly Medicine team. The post holder will work across a variety of elderly, medical wards to assess patients, facilitate discharges and provide rehabilitation in the acute environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work will involve a mixture of complex and routine cases, with experienced team support from Physiotherapists, Occupational therapists and Therapy Assistants. We are looking for a motivated, enthusiastic therapist to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The integrated Rehabilitation Service aims to provide a progressive, forward thinking approach to patient care whilst able to support its staff in personal development and continued education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note due to high volume of applications for some posts, this post may close before the displayed closing date. We recommend that you apply for this role as soon as possible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact if you would like to discuss the post further:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alice.eatock@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deborah.brown@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
